  "body": "### Steps:\r\n1. Recover the user account that holds the USDC.e asset located on the Optimism network.(If necessary, contact me if you need an account that has USDÐ¡.e asset, can share it in private messages)\r\n2. Open the Eth address in the wallet\r\n\r\n\r\n### Actual result:\r\nThe price of the USDC.e  (Bridged from Ethereum)  asset is displayed as 0 in the wallet (Both within mobile and desktop)\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/300b4da2-ce71-4237-aad4-202d4c5c170a)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected result:\r\nPotential solution:\r\nthe USDC.e asset is expected to be supported and fetched from Uniswap according to https://github.com/status-im/status-go/blob/develop/services/wallet/token/uniswap.go. \r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/0c0a5fa6-a5a4-455b-895f-26f928dcb043)\r\n\r\nHowever, we fetch the prices from the CryptoCompare resource (https://min-api.cryptocompare.com/data/blockchain/list), where the USDC.e asset is not present, probably this is a reason why correct price is not fetched. In such cases, instead of showing 0 as the asset price, I suggest displaying an empty space\r\n\r\n",
